text: Gé Dekker (10 December 1904 - 18 March 1995) was a Dutch swimmer. He competed in two events at the 1924 Summer Olympics, the 100 metre freestyle and the 4 × 200 metre freestyle relay. ==References== Category:1904 births Category:1995 deaths Category:Dutch male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of the Netherlands Category:Swimmers at the 1924 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Zaanstad
